25:29.920 --> 25:38.600
♪

25:38.640 --> 25:48.640
♪

25:48.680 --> 25:54.640
♪

25:54.680 --> 25:57.680
[Indistinct conversations]

25:57.720 --> 26:06.640
♪

26:06.680 --> 26:16.680
♪

26:16.720 --> 26:24.880
♪

26:24.920 --> 26:27.960
Raise your hands
and look forward.

26:28.000 --> 26:29.720
[Whirring]

26:29.760 --> 26:36.320
♪

26:36.360 --> 26:39.120
[Indistinct conversations]

26:39.160 --> 26:48.680
♪

26:48.720 --> 26:53.960
♪

26:54.000 --> 26:55.280
Thank you
for seeing me.

26:55.320 --> 26:57.920
♪

26:57.960 --> 26:59.560
You didn't give me
much choice.

26:59.600 --> 27:08.320
♪

27:08.360 --> 27:11.560
But,
like I told Birdy,

27:11.600 --> 27:13.320
no deals to be had.

27:13.360 --> 27:16.240
You haven't heard
what I'm offerin' yet.

27:16.280 --> 27:18.840
The only offer
is this --

27:18.880 --> 27:21.160
you can save
your son's life

27:21.200 --> 27:23.560
by returning my drugs.

27:23.600 --> 27:25.640
If you don't accept,

27:25.680 --> 27:29.640
I will ensure that the
bounty on Anthony's head

27:29.680 --> 27:33.040
is doublethat
of the others.

27:33.080 --> 27:35.040
Right now,
it's half a million

27:35.080 --> 27:36.800
for anyone who kills

27:36.840 --> 27:40.080
Jimmy, Michael, Frank,
or Viking.

27:40.120 --> 27:41.320
But that's not
the real cost

27:41.360 --> 27:43.240
of killing a Kinsella.

27:43.280 --> 27:46.120
That figure would be
closer to...

27:46.160 --> 27:48.120
50 million?

27:48.160 --> 27:50.600
Because, if any of them
are killed,

27:50.640 --> 27:53.360
I will burn your drugs,

27:53.400 --> 27:55.600
all of it at once.

27:55.640 --> 27:57.680
Are you fuckin'
threatenin' me?

27:57.720 --> 28:00.160
I'm negotiatin'.

28:00.200 --> 28:02.520
You're a businessman.

28:02.560 --> 28:05.000
You know
how it works.

28:05.040 --> 28:07.280
Who's to say I can't
get my drugs back

28:07.320 --> 28:09.160
and clip them all?

28:09.200 --> 28:11.280
Me.

28:11.320 --> 28:14.080
Right now,
your drugs are safe,

28:14.120 --> 28:16.600
but, as soon as any one
of us are killed,

28:16.640 --> 28:19.040
one of the others
will burn them all.

28:19.080 --> 28:22.880
Even you would feel the
bite of 50 million lost.

28:22.920 --> 28:24.840
Has to be someone,
somewhere, waiting

28:24.880 --> 28:27.400
on their cut
of those drugs.

28:27.440 --> 28:30.840
Why disappoint them?

28:30.880 --> 28:32.760
So, what are you
offering me?

28:32.800 --> 28:34.360
50 million,

28:34.400 --> 28:35.920
in return for peace.

28:35.960 --> 28:37.600
[Scoffing]
That's your offer,

28:37.640 --> 28:39.640
give back what you stole?
That's fuckin' nothin'.

28:39.680 --> 28:41.320
You've had
Dotser killed,

28:41.360 --> 28:44.400
and Noel Lawlor,
Jock McCluskey,

28:44.440 --> 28:47.000
two of our dealers
from the Grace Park estate,

28:47.040 --> 28:51.240
and I have buried my son
five weeks ago today.

28:51.280 --> 28:53.560
That's not nothin'.

28:53.600 --> 28:54.880
We've paid a price.

28:57.440 --> 29:00.560
What happened
to your son

29:00.600 --> 29:02.560
was wrong.

29:02.600 --> 29:03.800
That was an accident.

29:03.840 --> 29:05.800
Doesn't make the cost
any less.

29:09.920 --> 29:12.880
Everything I am,

29:12.920 --> 29:14.640
everything I've built --
allof it --

29:14.680 --> 29:18.040
is dependent
on one thing --

29:18.080 --> 29:21.440
that people know
I'm fuckin' ruthless.

29:21.480 --> 29:25.000
Without that, it all
comes tumblin' down,

29:25.040 --> 29:28.280
and agreeing
to your offer,

29:28.320 --> 29:30.280
even if it's fair,

29:30.320 --> 29:33.840
makes me look weak.

29:33.880 --> 29:36.240
So I can't accept it.

29:36.280 --> 29:38.680
Just can't.

29:38.720 --> 29:42.240
What canyou accept?

29:42.280 --> 29:44.000
I want

29:44.040 --> 29:46.240
what was stolen
returned...

29:50.240 --> 29:53.480
...and one

29:53.520 --> 29:57.360
of Jimmy, Michael,
Frank, or Eric.

29:57.400 --> 30:01.840
♪

30:01.880 --> 30:04.760
Which means I'm sparin'
three of them.

30:04.800 --> 30:06.440
So, you've done
well here.

30:06.480 --> 30:15.720
♪

30:15.760 --> 30:19.360
Which one
do you want killed?

30:19.400 --> 30:20.760
That's for you
to decide.

30:20.800 --> 30:23.880
♪

30:23.920 --> 30:28.200
It's my son's
month's mind mass today.

30:28.240 --> 30:30.880
I'd like to bring
Anthony to it,

30:30.920 --> 30:32.560
without worrying
about his safety.

30:32.600 --> 30:36.640
♪

30:36.680 --> 30:39.440
I'll let it be known
it's over.

30:39.480 --> 30:41.440
Thank you.

30:41.480 --> 30:42.880
And you let me know

30:42.920 --> 30:44.080
which of the four
you choose.

30:44.120 --> 30:46.680
♪

30:46.720 --> 30:48.960
[Indistinct PA announcement]

30:49.000 --> 30:58.600
♪

30:58.640 --> 31:01.760
♪

31:01.800 --> 31:03.200
[Brakes squeal]

31:03.240 --> 31:05.200
♪

31:05.240 --> 31:07.160
[Engine stops,
seat belt clicks, whirs]

31:07.200 --> 31:09.840
♪

31:09.880 --> 31:11.520
[Exhales]

31:11.560 --> 31:15.880
♪

31:15.920 --> 31:16.960
Kitchen.

31:17.000 --> 31:27.000
♪

31:27.040 --> 31:30.160
What happened?

31:30.200 --> 31:32.120
Eamon's agreed
to end the feud.

31:34.160 --> 31:35.240
What does he want?

31:35.280 --> 31:38.080
His drugs back.

31:38.120 --> 31:41.240
And Eric.

31:41.280 --> 31:44.000
No.

31:44.040 --> 31:45.400
No fucking way!

31:45.440 --> 31:48.320
How Eamon sees it is
somebody has to die,

31:48.360 --> 31:50.400
and Viking was the one
who started all of this.

31:50.440 --> 31:52.480
I don't care how he
fuckin' sees it.

31:52.520 --> 31:54.720
She fucking
set this up!

31:54.760 --> 31:55.760
This is
what she wanted.

31:55.800 --> 31:57.720
She's been after Eric
all along.

31:57.760 --> 31:59.640
Did...you...
agreeto this?

31:59.680 --> 32:01.440
No.
I'm just telling you

32:01.480 --> 32:03.080
what Eamon's offer is.

32:03.120 --> 32:05.480
It's Frank's decision,
whether we take it or not.

32:05.520 --> 32:08.080
I can see what
you're fuckin' doin'.

32:08.120 --> 32:10.120
It's hard,

32:10.160 --> 32:13.720
even considerin' the idea
of losin' a child.

32:13.760 --> 32:17.240
You can try to imagine
how painful it's gonna be,

32:17.280 --> 32:20.320
how empty you'll feel,

32:20.360 --> 32:23.120
how much you'll blame yourself
every day for what happened.

32:23.160 --> 32:26.800
♪

32:26.840 --> 32:29.080
But you won't even get
fuckin' close.

32:29.120 --> 32:34.920
♪

32:34.960 --> 32:38.680
But you're the boss,
Frank.

32:38.720 --> 32:42.280
I'm sure you'll do
what's best for everyone.

32:42.320 --> 32:44.960
Fuck you.

32:45.000 --> 32:46.640
I am
the fucking boss,

32:46.680 --> 32:47.880
and I can see right
through your game.

32:47.920 --> 32:49.160
I know what you're
fucking at!

32:49.200 --> 32:50.080
You need to go.

32:50.120 --> 32:51.800
♪

32:51.840 --> 32:54.800
This was her plan
all along!

32:54.840 --> 32:55.840
That's why she wanted
to meet Eamon --

32:55.880 --> 32:57.400
to fuck Eric!

32:57.440 --> 32:59.080
I warned you --
this is what she wants!

32:59.120 --> 33:01.080
You need to calm down.

33:01.120 --> 33:02.400
Are you listening
to me?

33:02.440 --> 33:05.600
[Crying] Stop being
so fuckin' pathetic!

33:05.640 --> 33:07.600
You're the boss,
then show it.

33:07.640 --> 33:09.520
Stop...
stompin' your feet

33:09.560 --> 33:11.520
and shoutin',
and dosomething.

33:11.560 --> 33:13.160
She set him up.
She set Eric up.

33:13.200 --> 33:15.960
Eamon was always going
to want a head.

33:16.000 --> 33:18.840
Eric's
the obvious one!

33:18.880 --> 33:20.800
Well, I'm not going
to let them kill him.

33:20.840 --> 33:22.160
Well, then, find a way
to save him.

33:22.200 --> 33:29.480
♪

33:29.520 --> 33:30.600
Officer:
Next.

33:30.640 --> 33:37.440
♪

33:37.480 --> 33:38.480
Next.

33:38.520 --> 33:42.920
♪

33:42.960 --> 33:45.920
[Wand whining]

33:45.960 --> 33:49.560
♪

33:49.600 --> 33:52.600
[Children speaking indistinctly]

33:52.640 --> 33:54.640
♪

33:54.680 --> 33:55.800
[Coughing nearby]

33:55.840 --> 34:02.680
♪

34:02.720 --> 34:05.920
♪

34:05.960 --> 34:07.360
Sit down there
and relax!

34:07.400 --> 34:10.480
Child:
[Speaks indistinctly]

34:10.520 --> 34:11.880
Do some colorin'
or somethin'.

34:11.920 --> 34:13.000
We want to play, Ma!

34:13.040 --> 34:14.280
Yeah?
Well --

34:14.320 --> 34:16.160
Officer:
All 11:30s.

34:16.200 --> 34:18.600
[Baby wailing]

34:18.640 --> 34:25.360
♪

34:25.400 --> 34:27.600
[Footsteps approach]

34:27.640 --> 34:33.680
♪

34:33.720 --> 34:35.120
[Clang in distance]

34:35.160 --> 34:36.920
Are you --
Are you alright?

34:43.680 --> 34:44.920
[Clang in distance]

34:46.560 --> 34:49.760
[Sigh]

34:49.800 --> 34:50.960
You were right.

34:55.000 --> 34:56.400
I wasn't thinkin'
about you.

35:00.840 --> 35:02.800
And...

35:02.840 --> 35:04.880
I don't want you to be
on your own for years.

35:10.720 --> 35:11.880
[Gulp]

35:15.240 --> 35:16.400
[Gulp]

35:17.760 --> 35:21.000
[Inhales sharply]

35:21.040 --> 35:22.520
There's an eyewitness
to the shootin'.

35:26.640 --> 35:27.920
He's the one
that's put me in here.

35:30.640 --> 35:33.800
I need you to get Kem
and find out who he is.

35:37.160 --> 35:38.800
Once you know,

35:38.840 --> 35:41.880
take 20 grand from the
stash in the ceilin'

35:41.920 --> 35:43.320
and get Kem
to hire someone

35:43.360 --> 35:47.800
to have them clipped.

35:47.840 --> 35:52.200
Don'thave any direct
contact yourself.

35:52.240 --> 35:53.760
Let Kem do all that.

35:53.800 --> 35:56.160
He'll know who
to get.

35:56.200 --> 35:57.200
Do you hear me?

35:59.680 --> 36:01.800
Tell him there's another
10 grand in it

36:01.840 --> 36:02.880
when the job's
done properly.

36:06.400 --> 36:08.880
If you do that,

36:08.920 --> 36:10.200
I can get outta here.

36:15.960 --> 36:19.160
Can you do that
for me?

36:19.200 --> 36:20.160
Yeah.

36:22.680 --> 36:27.880
♪

36:27.920 --> 36:28.960
[Sigh]

36:29.000 --> 36:38.440
♪

36:38.480 --> 36:41.080
